# .gitattributes — line-ending normalisation policy.
#
# Without these rules, Git on Windows (where `core.autocrlf=true` is the
# default) checks shell scripts out with CRLF. The Linux kernel's `#!/bin/bash`
# loader rejects `\r` as part of the interpreter path and fails with
# "/bin/bash^M: bad interpreter: No such file or directory" — even though
# `bash` is installed and on PATH. The .desktop / .service files used by the
# Linux desktop-integration helper (`linux-setup.sh`) have a similar problem:
# `update-desktop-database` accepts them but Wayland compositors silently
# ignore lines that don't match exactly.
#
# Rules below pin EOL per file type. `text=auto` lets Git auto-detect text vs.
# binary for anything not explicitly listed.

# ── Default ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auto-detect text vs binary. Text files get the platform-native EOL on
# checkout unless overridden below.
* text=auto

# ── LF-mandatory ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shell scripts and anything else the kernel exec-loads or that XDG tools
# expect LF for. Forcing eol=lf means the working tree always has LF on
# every platform, including Windows.
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.bash      text eol=lf
*.zsh       text eol=lf
*.fish      text eol=lf
*.desktop   text eol=lf
*.service   text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf
*.mk        text eol=lf

# ── CRLF-mandatory ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Classic Windows scripting hosts (`cmd.exe`, Windows PowerShell 5.1) prefer
# CRLF. PowerShell 7+ accepts either, but the .bat / .cmd convention is
# unambiguous so we pin them.
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.cmd       text eol=crlf

# ── Binary (no normalisation) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Force-mark these so Git never tries to "normalise" them on checkout.
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.icns      binary
*.zip       binary
*.tar       binary
*.tar.gz    binary
*.tgz       binary
*.gz        binary
*.7z        binary
*.pdf       binary
*.dll       binary
*.exe       binary
*.pdb       binary
*.snk       binary
*.pfx       binary
*.p12       binary
